articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: China's consumer prices swung into decline and factory-gate deflation persisted in October, suggesting pressures on demand have picked up as the world's second-largest economy struggles to emerge from a post-pandemic slump.
articles.title: China's Oct consumer prices fall faster than expected

articles.author: Dawn Chmielewski, Lisa Richwine
articles.description: Walt Disney (DIS.N) exceeded Wall Street's earnings expectations on Wednesday as higher attendance at its Shanghai and Hong Kong theme parks offset a decline in advertising revenue at television network ABC.
articles.title: Disney tops earnings forecasts as Iger sets 'building' phase

articles.author: Patrick Wingrove, Leroy Leo
articles.description: The U.S. Food and Drug Administration on Wednesday approved Eli Lilly's (LLY.N) drug for weight loss, giving the U.S. drugmaker official entry into a lucrative market that has captured Wall Street's enthusiasm this year.
articles.title: US FDA approves Lilly weight-loss drug

articles.author: Scott Murdoch
articles.description: Asian share markets rallied on Thursday and the dollar was weaker after most U.S stocks edged higher and the S&P 500 recorded its longest winning streak in two years, with investors on high alert for signs that global interest rates have peaked.
articles.title: Asian shares rise as S&P 500 records longest win streak in two years

articles.author: Leika Kihara
articles.description: Some Bank of Japan policymakers last month called for the need to start phasing out massive stimulus and lay the groundwork for a future exit from ultra-low interest rates, a summary of opinions at their October meeting showed on Thursday.
articles.title: BOJ debated groundwork for future easy-policy exit at Oct meeting

articles.author: David Shepardson
articles.description: The White House said President Joe Biden would veto a Senate Republican effort on Wednesday to reverse his administration's decision to waive some "Buy America" requirements for government-funded electric vehicle charging stations.
articles.title: Biden would veto bid to reverse 'Buy America' EV charging waiver

articles.author: Jarrett Renshaw
articles.description: Congressional pressure is growing on the U.S. Treasury to help salvage trucking giant Yellow from bankruptcy, from Republicans and Democrats alike, letters viewed by Reuters show.
articles.title: Pressure grows on US Treasury to salvage trucking giant Yellow

articles.author: Humeyra Pamuk, Nidal Al-Mughrabi, Maytaal Angel
articles.description: Street battles raged in Gaza City with Hamas fighters using tunnels to ambush Israeli forces, as the United States said Palestinians must govern Gaza post-war, countering Israeli comments that it would control security indefinitely.
articles.title: Fierce fighting in Gaza City; US says Palestinians must govern Gaza post-war

articles.author: James Oliphant, Tim Reid
articles.description: Donald Trump's leading rivals for the Republican presidential nomination sought to make the case for being their party's standard-bearer at the outset of Wednesday's Republican debate, with time running out to disrupt the former president's march toward another White House bid.
articles.title: Republican debate: Will DeSantis and Haley take fight to Trump or each other?

articles.author: Idrees Ali
articles.description: The United States, for the second time in recent weeks, carried out strikes on Wednesday against a weapon storage facility in eastern Syria that the Pentagon said was used by Iran's Islamic Revolutionary Guard Corps (IRGC) and affiliated groups.
articles.title: US carries out new strikes against facility used by Iran in Syria
